-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">operates under a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the Department of Business, Innovation and Skills, on behalf of government as a whole.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">U</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">KAS </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">assesses and accredits competent </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">person schemes under Part P of the Building Regulations on behalf of the Department of Communities and Local Government (DCLG). Accreditation by UKAS </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to the European standard BS EN 45011 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is a condition of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">authorisation </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s a competent person scheme by DCLG.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">BS EN 45011 is the European standard for organisations operating product certification systems. In this sense, UKAS accredits the competent person scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> operators</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to carry out the certification of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the installation se</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rvices provided by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">businesses</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">including their ability to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">self-certify </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">their work as compliant with the Building Regulations</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. BS EN 45011 </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">sets down requirements for certification bodies in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">terms</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">their</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> independence, impartiality, technical competence and</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> management </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">capability</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. Accreditation by UKAS provides an assurance that th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e scheme operators</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> meet the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">se</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> requirements in relation to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the activities required of them to operate a competent person scheme. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">An important part of the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certification process is t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">o assess the technical competence of the contractors that are members of the competent person schemes against th</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e requirements set out in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">DCLG’s conditions of authorisation and the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Minimum Technical Competence requirements</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> set out for the installers themselves</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">As part of the accreditation process, UKAS </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">determines</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> that this assessment is being carried out. UKAS carries out sample testing of the scheme operators and witnessed assessments to ensure this is the case. In this w</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ay, accreditation ensures that consistent standards of competence are maintained.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">CLG’s conditions of authorisation require scheme operators to take a risk-based approach to the surveillance of their member companies. This is based on factors such as ins</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">pection outcomes, significant complaints and major changes in personnel. However, scheme operators must undertake a minimum of one on-site inspection of each member’s work every three years and new members need to be inspected annually for the first two ye</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ars following initial assessment to establish a clean track record. Additional inspections can be carried out at the discretion of the scheme operators. The accreditation process ensures that the correct level of surveillance is carried out by the scheme o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">perators.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS considers that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">competition between the different operators of competent person schemes is a positive factor in terms of providing an element of choice for electrical contractors and keeping the cost of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certification</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> at a reasonable level. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">UKAS accreditation process is aimed at ensuring the consistency of outcome</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, where there are a number of providers,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> and therefore maintaining common standards. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Whilst DCLG maintains an overview of the competent person schemes and has ultimate responsib</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ility for the authorisation of these schemes, the day to day assessment and supervision of the schemes is carried out by UKAS on DCLG’s behalf. The UKAS accreditation process is, of necessity, based on sample testing of the organisations concerned but is n</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">onetheless a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rigorous</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> process</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. UKAS considers that accreditation provides the necessary level of assurance of competence without being unduly intrusive or expensive. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>